<h1 id="toc15"><span>Special Affairs Division, Public Security Bureau of Metropolitan Police Department<a name="tokuzika"></a></span></h1>
<div class="image-container floatright"><img src="http://scp-jp.wikidot.com/local--files/groups-of-interest-jp/%E8%AD%A6%E8%A6%96%E5%BA%81%E5%85%AC%E5%AE%89%E9%83%A8%E7%89%B9%E4%BA%8B%E8%AA%B2.png" width="60px" alt="警視庁公安部特事課.png" class="image" /></div>
<p><strong>Overview:</strong> The Special Affairs Division or simply SAD, Public Security Bureau of Metropolitan Police Department is an undercover investigative agency within the Metropolitan Police Department organized to deal with abnormal phenomena and paranormal crimes.</p>
<p>SAD is under the control of the Special Affairs Investigation Bureau of National Police Agency, which is a member of JAGPATO, and is indirectly influenced by the policies of the Japanese Government and JAGPATO. Their main activities are aimed at grasping trends and restraining the behavior of GoIs throughout Japan, mitigating the impact of anomalous entities on society, and protecting the general public from threatening anomalies. &#8212; But due to bureaucratic issues and lack of financial resources, personnel, and equipment, their activities are often difficult.</p>
<p>The Foundation is building a cooperative system with SAD but the mutual exchange is limited due to concerns about information leakage.</p>
